This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing (NLP) and the use of ELMo embeddings, which are commonly used in NLP tasks. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses different methods for combining the ELMo embeddings, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of ELMo embeddings in image captioning, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the training speed-up achieved by reducing the complexity of the language model, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
